docs.text: in china in 1982 i turned the tables on our national guide and asked him if he had any questions about america .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i guess i was expecting some sort of political question .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: instead , i was dumfounded by what was most on his mind .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: " in america , do wives and their mothers-in-law get along well ? "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he assured me in china that they did , but i am certain if that were true he would not have asked .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: even in china people seem to have problems relating to in- laws .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: perhaps some of life's most difficult relationships arise when families are suddenly artificially joined by marriage .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a man trying to relate to his new prospective in-laws and vice-versa could be the basis of a very strong comedy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: meet the parents does not demonstrate that fact , however .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: greg focker ( played by ben stiller ) has been dating and in love with pam byrnes ( teri polo ) for ten months and is now ready to propose to her .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he will do it during a weekend visit to meet debbie's family and to attend her sister's wedding .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: from the beginning the relationship is awkward between greg and jack and dina byrnes ( robert deniro and blythe danner ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: through no fault of his own , the airline has lost greg's luggage .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and he has to ask to borrow clothing .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it is the beginning of a game of one-upmanship in which greg is nearly always one-down .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as the games go on greg is more and more uncomfortable and uneasy which only contributes to the mistakes he makes .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: greg is playing a game he does not understand , in a league he is new to .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but perhaps along the way he will discover some unexpected secrets about his father-in-law .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this film had potential in its tale of one-upmanship .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it has hit on a situation that many in the audience may find familiar--one that has not been done overly frequently in films .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but the script by jim herzfeld and john hamburg is a little too contrived .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: too many coincidences in the story work against greg .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the script could not decide if the main character was incompetent or simply unlucky .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: certainly he does not help his situation by doing everything wrong he possibly could , but even when he is trying to do the right things nature conspires against him .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there is an uneven mix of slapstick sequences and human comedy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: certainly the last part of the film feels awkwardly written .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the main reason to see meet the parents is to see robert deniro's performance .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: deniro plays the suspicious and not a little fascistic father as tightly wound and threatening as he can .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the little judgmental expressions on his face are a show in themselves as greg digs himself deeper and deeper into his insecurities .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but we do not really see much of that digging .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ben stiller is an affable presence in the film but is not really stretching himself by playing the role as the nebbish to whom so many bad things happen .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it is nice to see blythe danner again on the screen .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but her character has a basic conflict between a basic decency and her love for her husband and the script should have given her more to do with that .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: randy newman has written a playful score .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in the first few seconds of the film it does something creative i have never heard a film score do before .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there is a lot of source music that is popular music of the 1960s .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: presumably that is what the upper class listens to at least in somebody's imagination .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: humor is subjective and some this film has been getting some favorable comment .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but this is a comedy that works only occasionally for me .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i would have to rate it 4 on the 0 to 10 scale and a 0 on the -4 to +4 scale .
